{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change how news sites announce celebrity deaths",
        "additional_details": "Comments on posts about someone\u2019s death are sensitive. While many express love, tribute, and comfort to fans, a minority are filled with harmful trolling and unwarranted speculation. This creates a lasting record that could cause pain for the deceased\u2019s children and family in the future. In announcements such as these, we believe comments only fuel engagement and serve no meaningful purpose.",
        "background": "Create a law requiring news sites who publish articles or social media posts announcing celebrity, public figure, or notable person deaths, or who publish related news articles in the following weeks, must do so in a way that does not allow members of the public to post comments. ",
